Part I - FIFA19¶

by Rawabi Alharbi¶

Introduction¶

In this project, I will use FIFA 19 dataset, which I imported from Kaggle. FIFA 19 is part of the FIFA series of association football video games. It is one of the most popular games in the world. the dataset contaons detailed attributes for every player registered in the latest edition of FIFA 19 database.

In [12]:
# remove the  sign, K, M, and '.' from the value, wage, and release_clause columns
def money_format_fix(column):
    fifa_df[column] = (fifa_df[column].str[1:].replace(r'[KM]+$', '', regex=True).astype(float) *
                       fifa_df[column].str.extract(r'[\d\.]+([KM]+)', expand=False)
                       .fillna(1).replace(['K','M'], [10**3, 10**6]).astype(int))

money_format_fix('value')
money_format_fix('wage')
money_format_fix('release_clause')
In [13]:
# convert the weight unit from pounds to kg
fifa_df["weight"] = fifa_df["weight"].str[:3].astype(float) / 2.205

# Convert feet and inches to cm value
fifa_df['height_cm'] = fifa_df['height'].str.split("'")
fifa_df['feet'] = fifa_df['height_cm'].str.get(0).astype(float)
fifa_df['inch'] = fifa_df['height_cm'].str.get(1).astype(float)
fifa_df['height'] = (fifa_df['feet']*12+fifa_df['inch'])*2.54
fifa_df.drop(['height_cm','feet','inch'],axis=1,inplace=True)

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The original dataset contains 18207 entries with 88 features. During the cleaning, the unusful columns were deleted as well as the missing values. The new shape of the data after the cleaning is 16643 entries with 24 features to work with. Most variables are numeric in nature, the remaining variables are categorical and string.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I am interested in investigating the attributes which each playing positions need to have and what attributes influence whether a player is a top footballer.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I think the player Age and Position features may help to support my investigation and may have a huge effect on the player's value. Also, Height and Weight features may help to know whether they are playing a rule in detering the position of the player.

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

1. numeric variables: I started with invistigating the Weight variable. It has a normal distribution with most players weighing between 70kg and 80kg. Then, I investigated the Age variable. It was interesting as it's distribution is slightly positively skewed. After that, I had a look at the Height variable and it is Bimodal.

2. categorical variables: I started with invistigating the Nationality variable. I viewed the countries that appeared most frequently in the dataset. England is at the top. Then, I had a look at the Club and it was expected to see 6 clubs from England in the top 10 clubs. After that, I had a look at the playing position. Most palyers play the position ST which is the top striker. Also, I found out that most players are right footed.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

When I had a look at the players Height distribution, it was looking so abnormal. Then, I noticed it was poorly format e.g 81 = 8'1. I fixed by changing the whole unit into cm. Also, some columns were having missing values like clubs, joined, contract, and I dropped the rows that are including these missing values in order to have better analysis.

  • I started by looking at the correlation and relationship between Weight and Height. The plot shows a weak positive relationship between them. The player value and wage has a fairly strong relationship, so when a player is valued in a club, he also gets paid more.
  • I had a look at some relationship between quantitative and qualitative features in the data. Most of Right footed and Left footed players got a rating of 3. Also, most players have a normal body type and a few players have a stocky body type.
  • Wage has a positive correlation with Release clause. The more a player's earns, the higher clubs set the release clause.
  • Age has a negative correlation with Potential. Logically, the older the player get, the less he is referred to as a potential. Young players are mostly seen as players with potentials.
  • Real Madrid has the most Wage in compare to other clubs which is the reason that they have high number of high profile players.
  • Messi earns more than all other players with a wage more than 500k. Also, when I looked at the Nationality effect on player's valuation, it shows that Spanish and Brazilian players are valued most. Also, England players have the highest player ratings on FIFA19.
